  "data_caveat": "Single source (theoddsapi) over a ~12-day window; all prices are PRE-KICKOFF. Snapshots share one capture-grid across books, so lead-lag is measured at the API poll cadence (~3.2 min median in dense runs), NOT true tick latency: a lag of 0-1 snapshots cannot resolve sub-poll leadership. Cross-correlation pools first-differenced consensus moves across matches. Informativeness uses the last pre-kickoff snapshot as 'close'. Treat as indicative microstructure, not execution-grade latency."
